Previous analysis showed that XGBoost has a strong performance with 70% or 80% set for training plus following weights for Synthetic Minority Oversampling technique:

* Growing: SMOTE with 0.18, 0.75, 0.07 weights
* Dormant: SMOTE with 0.7, 0.25, 0.05 weights

Similar to initial submission a trail analysis was done to identify the best XGBoost model for dormant and growing separately.

There is along story of QA/QC for gauged set (and ungauged set to some degree). Urbanized catchments from various sources retrieved to get them added to both gauged and ungauged sets. Duplication and streamflow ratio were also controlled for catchments.

